Interface CourseSystemInterface

All Superinterfaces:
Systems
All Known Implementing Classes:
StaffSystem, StudentSystem
public interface CourseSystemInterface
extends Systems
Interface to be implemented for systems that handle course/index objects

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void selectCourse​(java.lang.String courseCode)
    Method to select a course to be used in the system
    void selectIndex​(java.lang.String indexNo)
    Method to select an index to be used in the system selectCourse(String) method should always be run first

    Methods inherited from interface managers.Systems

    clearSelections, getSystemStatus

  • Method Details

    • selectCourse

      void selectCourse​(java.lang.String courseCode) throws KeyNotFoundException
      Method to select a course to be used in the system
      Parameters:
      courseCode - course code of the course
      Throws:
      KeyNotFoundException - thrown if the course code does not match any in the system

    • selectIndex

      void selectIndex​(java.lang.String indexNo) throws KeyNotFoundException, MissingSelectionException
      Method to select an index to be used in the system selectCourse(String) method should always be run first
      Parameters:
      indexNo - index number of the index
      Throws:
      KeyNotFoundException - Used if no indexes match the given index number can be found for the course
      MissingSelectionException - Used if the course has not yet been selected
